  "body": "Would it be possible to define hooks that other 3pt can utilize?\r\n\r\nFor example, I am creating a plugin that should run right after buidler-deploy has watched for changes and deployed. But right now I THINK my only possibility to hook into this process is to copy everything and override. \r\n\r\nIt would be nice if buidler-deploy could state following in its watch process. \r\n```\r\nawait bre.run(\"deploy:before-watch-deploy\")\r\nawait bre.run(\"deploy:after-watch-deploy\")\r\n```\r\nThen I can create a task that runs when they execute. \r\n\r\nIf I create a run that does not have a task i get this \r\n```\r\n@symfoni/buidler-demo: BuidlerError: BDLR303: Unrecognized task deploy:before-before-watch-deploy\r\n@symfoni/buidler-demo:     at Environment.run (/Users/robin/code/buidler-plugins/packages/buidler-demo/node_modules/@nomiclabs/buidler/src/internal/core/runtime-environment.ts:118:13)\r\n@symfoni/buidler-demo:     at /Users/robin/code/buidler-plugins/packages/buidler-react/dist/src/index.js:55:23\r\n@symfoni/buidler-demo:     at step (/Users/robin/code/buidler-plugins/packages/buidler-react/dist/src/index.js:33:23)\r\n@symfoni/buidler-demo:     at Object.next (/Users/robin/code/buidler-plugins/packages/buidler-react/dist/src/index.js:14:53)\r\n@symfoni/buidler-demo:     at fulfilled (/Users/robin/code/buidler-plugins/packages/buidler-react/dist/src/index.js:5:58)\r\n@symfoni/buidler-demo:     at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:93:5)\r\n```",
